{{ProbabilityTopics}}
'''[[Probability]] and [[Statistics]]''' or also called '''[[Statistics]] and [[Probability]]''' are two related but separate [[academic discipline]]s. [[Statistical analysis]] often uses [[probability distribution]]s, and the two topics are often studied together. However, [[probability theory]] contains much that is mostly of [[mathematics|mathematical]] interest and not directly relevant to statistics. Moreover, many topics in statistics are independent of probability theory. {{dubious|date=July 2014}}

